data:image/png;base64,<boltAction type="file" filePath="README.md"># Screener.in Layout Fixer

A Chrome extension that fixes the financial data display on screener.in to show metrics in a single row with 4 columns.

## Features

- Automatically fixes the layout when you visit screener.in company pages
- Adjusts the grid to display 4 columns properly
- Prevents metrics from wrapping into multiple rows
- Works on all company profile pages

## Installation

Since this is a local extension, you'll need to install it in developer mode:

1. Download or clone this repository
2. Open Chrome and go to `chrome://extensions/`
3. Enable "Developer mode" in the top right
4. Click "Load unpacked" and select the folder containing these files
5. The extension should now be installed and active

## Usage

The extension automatically applies the layout fixes when you visit any screener.in company page. You can also click the extension icon and press "Apply Fixes Now" to manually trigger the fixes.

## How It Works

The extension applies the following CSS and JavaScript fixes:

- Sets the company profile width to 100%
- Configures the top ratios grid to use 4 equal columns
- Removes width constraints on containers
- Ensures proper alignment and prevents text overflow

